    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-11-08T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-11-08T04:00:00-05:00" n="105"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.116/175: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-08T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 8, 1938—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 8—10:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>666. Tientsin’s 208 [<hi rend="italic">202</hi>], November 2, 11 a.m.<note n="25"
                        xml:id="d105fn25">Not printed.</note> A secretary of the Japanese Embassy
                    today informed this Embassy that the original issuance of permits by the
                    Superintendent of Customs was a mistake, but that the permits already issued
                    would not be rescinded; however, no further permits would be issued to those
                    companies (such as Amasia and Frazar) which have heretofore failed to obtain
                    permits for the import of short wave sets ordered before the imposition of the
                    embargo.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tientsin. By mail to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
